Thanks for replying.  Yes, I would appreciate an archive of what has already
been discussed;  I missed most of the recent postings.
	Excuse me if this has already been beat to death, but has anyone 
in this discussion considered using fractals to generate terrain.
The basic idea is to circle a sphere using random faults (10000 faults works
rather nicely).  I've heard rumors that STARFLIGHT generates its planetary
surfaces using this method (I've only seen the game, I don't actually have it)
Of course, the disadvantage is the incredible amount of cpu time that this 
requires.  This could be offset at the cost of flexibility by building a
database of planetary surfaces.
	Just throwing out some ideas.  If you have any suggestions for
improvement, please don't hesitate to flame away.

				Ralph



