Subject: Factors affecting coastlines (re: simulator)
Status: RO


    One factor which affects the shape of the land (but which I don't know
a whole lot about myself) is coral.  Any good geology reference should be
able to tell you how coral atolls form around islands as the sea level
gradually rises.  I don't know coral affects continental coastlines, but I
seem to remember that it does to a fairly large extent.

    You will probably also want to look into barrier islands--those long thin
islands parallel to the shore such as you see off the coast of the Carolinas.
Unfortunately, I don't remember how these are formed.  I think it's time for
me to start studying geology again....

    Relatively small features such as these probably don't need to be added
to the tectonic simulation itself.  It's probably enough to wait until the
continents are in place and then put them in where the conditions are right
for them.  Of course, it all depends on how detailed a simulation you want.

Mark Isaak	{decwrl,sun}!imagen!isaak  or  imagen!isaak@decwrl.dec.com


